properties.areaDesc: Northern Humboldt Coast; Coastal Del Norte
properties.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued January 11 at 1:09PM PST until January 11 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Eureka CA
properties.description:
...HIGH SURF ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM PST THIS
EVENING...

* WHAT....A large northwest swell will bring a threat for large
breaking waves to area beaches today and this evening. Breakers
of 24 to 27 ft will be possible on west and northwest facing
beaches. A high tide of 7-8 ft is also contributing to localized
flooding along low lying coastal areas. The tide and waves will
subside throughout the afternoon.

* WHERE...Coastal Del Norte and Northern Humboldt Coast Counties.

* WHEN...Until 7 PM PST this evening.. .

* IMPACTS...Large breaking waves will generate hazardous
conditions on area beaches. This threat will be maximized on
steeply sloped beaches. Large breaking waves can cause injury,
wash people off beaches and rocks, and capsize small boats near
shore. Local flooding along low lying roads areas along the near
coast.
properties.instruction:
A High Surf Advisory means that high surf will affect beaches in
the advisory area, producing rip currents and localized beach
erosion.

A Coastal Flood Advisory indicates that onshore winds and tides
will combine to generate flooding of low areas along the shore.

Drivers should exercise extreme caution when encountering
flooded roadways.

NWSheadline: COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 PM PST THIS EVENING
